Your [formula](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_distance) is incorrect. It should be:

    pointsDistance = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(x2 - x1, 2) + Math.pow(y2 - y1, 2));

This is just an application of the Pythagorean theorem, and Java has a [`Math.hypot()`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Math.html#hypot-double-double-) convenience method that also protects against arithmetic overflow/underflow:

    pointsDistance = Math.hypot(x2-x1, y2-y1);

Thanks to [@LouisWasserman](https://stackoverflow.com/users/869736/louis-wasserman) for the helpful comment.

